OL,3,CBrianna Ghey's school says pupils
OL,4,C'less stressed' after mobile phone ban
OL,6,FA survey of more than 15,000 schools
OL,7,Fin England by the Children's
OL,8,FCommissioner suggests that the vast
OL,9,Fmajority already have policies in
OL,10,Fplace that restrict the use of mobile
OL,11,Fphones during the school day.
OL,13,FDaniel Kebede, general secretary of
OL,14,Fthe NEU, said it was his "personal
OL,15,Fview" that the Labour Government
OL,16,Fshould take a stronger stance on
OL,17,Frestricting mobile phone use in
OL,18,Fschools.
