OL,3,CBrianna Ghey's school says pupils
OL,4,C'less stressed' after mobile phone ban
OL,6,FLast month, Ms Badenoch questioned why
OL,7,Fthe Government opposed a Tory
OL,8,Famendment to the Children's Wellbeing
OL,9,Fand Schools Bill to require schools to
OL,10,Fban the use of phones.
OL,12,FIn response, Prime Minister Sir Keir
OL,13,FStarmer described the proposal as
OL,14,F"completely unnecessary" as he claimed
OL,15,F"almost every school" already bans
OL,16,Fphones.
